    <div class="service-content">
      <p>Going through a divorce is one of the most stressful experiences in life. When real property is involved, getting an accurate, independent appraisal is one of the most important steps toward a fair resolution. Las Vegas Appraisal Co. provides certified divorce appraisals that are accepted by Nevada courts, attorneys, and mediators throughout Clark County.</p>

      <p>We understand the sensitivity of this process. Our appraisers are professional, discreet, and focused solely on delivering an accurate, defensible valuation — not on taking sides.</p>

      <h2>Why You Need a Certified Appraisal for Divorce</h2>
      <p>In Nevada, marital property — including the family home — must be divided equitably in a divorce. To do that fairly, both parties need to know the true current market value of the property. A certified appraisal provides that objective figure, reducing disputes and giving attorneys and courts a reliable foundation for settlement decisions.</p>

      <p>Without a professional appraisal, couples often rely on online estimates like Zillow, which can be off by tens of thousands of dollars in a market as dynamic as Las Vegas.</p>

      <h2>Our Divorce Appraisal Process</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>One or both spouses (or their attorneys) can request the appraisal</li>
        <li>We coordinate scheduling to minimize conflict and inconvenience</li>
        <li>The property is inspected and a full written report is prepared</li>
        <li>Reports are court-ready and comply with USPAP standards</li>
        <li>We can provide expert witness testimony if required</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Separate Appraisals for Each Party</h2>
      <p>In contested divorces, each spouse may wish to obtain their own independent appraisal. We can provide one or both appraisals, or work alongside another appraiser retained by the other party. Our reports are thorough and defensible, holding up under scrutiny in mediation or litigation.</p>

      <h2>Fast Turnaround When You Need It Most</h2>
      <p>We know divorce proceedings move quickly. We offer priority scheduling and typically deliver completed reports within 2–3 business days of the inspection. Call or text us 7 days a week at (702) 894-9279.</p>

      <h2>Service Area</h2>
      <p>We provide divorce appraisals throughout Clark County, including Las Vegas, Henderson, Summerlin, North Las Vegas, Pahrump, and surrounding communities.</p>

